<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
     8. PROCESS TIMELINE
═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="hp-process-section" id="dbms-process-section">
  <div class="hp-process-inner">
    <div class="hp-process-heading">
      <h2>From Vision to Victory: Our Proven Process</h2>
      <p>Discover how we turn your ideas into reality with our streamlined, client-focused development process. From initial consultation to final deployment, our expert team ensures every step is meticulously planned and executed to deliver outstanding results.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="hp-process-body">
      <div class="hp-process-steps" id="dbms-process-steps">
        <div class="hp-process-line-track">
          <div class="hp-process-line-fill" id="dbms-process-line-fill"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="hp-process-step" data-step="0">
          <div class="hp-step-dot-wrap"><div class="hp-step-dot"><i class="fa-solid fa-phone"></i></div></div>
          <div class="hp-step-content">
            <div class="hp-step-label">Step 1</div>
            <div class="hp-step-card">
              <h4>Have a Conversation</h4>
              <p>We want to hear your ideas, learn your company's workflow, and offer our software expertise to find a solution to your frustrations while facilitating your growth.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="hp-process-step" data-step="1">
          <div class="hp-step-dot-wrap"><div class="hp-step-dot"><i class="fa-solid fa-file-lines"></i></div></div>
          <div class="hp-step-content">
            <div class="hp-step-label">Step 2</div>
            <div class="hp-step-card">
              <h4>Propose Solution</h4>
              <p>Post conversation, we will send you a custom proposal with recommended technologies, a rough timeline, and a cost estimate to define the project specifications.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="hp-process-step" data-step="2">
          <div class="hp-step-dot-wrap"><div class="hp-step-dot"><i class="fa-solid fa-pen-ruler"></i></div></div>
          <div class="hp-step-content">
            <div class="hp-step-label">Step 3</div>
            <div class="hp-step-card">
              <h4>Design</h4>
              <p>Create lo-fi designs to outline basic structure, develop hi-fi designs for detailed visual representation, and build interactive prototypes for user testing and feedback.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="hp-process-step" data-step="3">
          <div class="hp-step-dot-wrap"><div class="hp-step-dot"><i class="fa-solid fa-code"></i></div></div>
          <div class="hp-step-content">
            <div class="hp-step-label">Step 4</div>
            <div class="hp-step-card">
              <h4>Develop, Test, and Deploy</h4>
              <p>Utilizing agile methodologies with iterative development cycles, continuous integration and testing, regular feedback sessions, and seamless deployment practices.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="hp-process-step" data-step="4">
          <div class="hp-step-dot-wrap"><div class="hp-step-dot"><i class="fa-solid fa-rocket"></i></div></div>
          <div class="hp-step-content">
            <div class="hp-step-label">Step 5</div>
            <div class="hp-step-card">
              <h4>Post-Launch</h4>
              <p>We stand by our work. After project completion, we warranty our work and remain available for future maintenance &amp; optimizations.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="hp-process-right">
        <div class="hp-process-right-actions">
          <span class="hp-btn-back-arrow" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" width="1em" height="1em">
              <path d="M23 12H5M12 19l-7-7 7-7"/>
            </svg>
          </span>
          <a href="/contact-us/" class="btn-orange">Get Started Today</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<script is:inline>
(function () {
  const stepsContainer = document.getElementById('dbms-process-steps');
  const lineFill = document.getElementById('dbms-process-line-fill');
  const steps = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('#dbms-process-steps .hp-process-step'));
  if (!stepsContainer || !lineFill || !steps.length) return;
  function update() {
    const containerRect = stepsContainer.getBoundingClientRect();
    const scrolled = Math.max(0, Math.min(1, (window.innerHeight * 0.6 - containerRect.top) / containerRect.height));
    lineFill.style.height = (scrolled * 100) + '%';
    steps.forEach((step) => {
      const rect = step.getBoundingClientRect();
      if (rect.top + rect.height / 2 < window.innerHeight * 0.65) step.classList.add('active');
      else step.classList.remove('active');
    });
  }
  window.addEventListener('scroll', update, { passive: true });
  update();
})();
</script>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
     9. FAQ
═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="cd-faq">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="faq-list">

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="true">
          <i class="fas fa-minus icon-open"></i>
          <i class="fas fa-plus icon-closed"></i>
          Which database should I use for my application?
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a" style="display:block;">The right choice depends on your data structure, consistency requirements, scale, and query patterns. We evaluate these factors during discovery and recommend the engine — or combination of engines — that will serve your application best, both now and at scale.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          <i class="fas fa-minus icon-open"></i>
          <i class="fas fa-plus icon-closed"></i>
          Can you migrate our existing database to the cloud?
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes. We manage the full migration lifecycle — assessment, schema transformation, data validation, cutover planning, and post-migration performance tuning — with strategies designed to minimize risk and downtime.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          <i class="fas fa-minus icon-open"></i>
          <i class="fas fa-plus icon-closed"></i>
          How do you handle database performance issues?
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a">We begin with a thorough audit using execution plans, slow query logs, and profiling tools to pinpoint root causes, then implement targeted optimizations — indexes, query rewrites, caching, or architectural changes — and measure the before/after impact.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          <i class="fas fa-minus icon-open"></i>
          <i class="fas fa-plus icon-closed"></i>
          What is the difference between SQL and NoSQL?
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a">SQL databases enforce a structured schema with ACID transactions, making them ideal for relational data where consistency is critical. NoSQL databases offer flexible schemas and horizontal scalability, excelling at unstructured data, high write volumes, or use cases where eventual consistency is acceptable.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          <i class="fas fa-minus icon-open"></i>
          <i class="fas fa-plus icon-closed"></i>
          How do you ensure our data is secure?
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a">We implement network isolation, role-based access control with least privilege, encryption at rest and in transit, column-level masking for sensitive fields, and comprehensive audit logging — plus regular security reviews to stay ahead of emerging threats.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

